  "doc_id": "46096",
  "text": "The activity of NK cells was measured using a well-known flow cytometeric method [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Briefly, isolated PBMCs (1×10 6 cells/ml) were stained with 0.4% PKH-26 fluorescent cell linker dye (SigmaAldrich, St Louis, MO). The target cells used were K562 tumour cells (1×10 5 cells/ml). The effector cells and the target cells were incubated at three effector to target ratios; 12.5: 1, 25:1 and 50:1 for four hours at 37°C. Control samples without PBMCs were also included to determine the number of cells that had undergone necrosis. Cells were stained with annexin V and 7-AAD (Becton Dickinson (BD) Pharmingen, San Diego, CA) and analysed on the BD FACS Calibur flow cytometer. Percent lysis was calculated for each sample at the different ratios as described previously [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
